I"Î<ol>
  <li>Add <code class="highlighter-rouge">mopidy</code> repository:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>curl <span class="nt">-fsSL</span> https://apt.mopidy.com/mopidy.gpg | <span class="nb">sudo </span>apt-key add -
curl <span class="nt">-fsSL</span> https://apt.mopidy.com/jessie.list <span class="o">&gt;</span> /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mopidy.list
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Install:
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>apt update
apt <span class="nb">install </span>mopidy mopidy-spotify mopidy-spotify-tunigo
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Edit <code class="highlighter-rouge">/etc/mopidy/mopidy.conf</code> (get Spotify <code class="highlighter-rouge">client_id</code> and <code class="highlighter-rouge">client_secret</code> <a href="https://www.mopidy.com/authenticate/">here</a>):
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>[mpd]
hostname = 0.0.0.0

[spotify]
username = &lt;$SPOTIFY_USERNAME&gt;
password = &lt;$SPOTIFY_PASSWORD&gt;
client_id = &lt;$SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID&gt;
client_secret = &lt;$SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET&gt;
bitrate = 320

[spotify_tunigo]
enabled = true
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Enable &amp; start <code class="highlighter-rouge">mopidy</code> service
    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>systemctl <span class="nb">enable</span> <span class="nt">--now</span> mopidy
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Run <code class="highlighter-rouge">ncmpcpp --host=&lt;$MOPIDY_HOST&gt;</code> (locally or via network)</li>
</ol>

<blockquote>
  <p>In <code class="highlighter-rouge">ncmpcpp</code> browse Spotify playlist by pressing <code class="highlighter-rouge">2</code>.<br />
Search songs and albums by pressing <code class="highlighter-rouge">3</code>.</p>
</blockquote>

